description.plain:
Ella Mai Howell (born November 3, 1994) is a British R&B singer and songwriter from Surrey, England. While enrolled at the British and Irish Modern Music Institute in 2014, Mai auditioned for The X-Factor as a part of a trio.

From 2015 to 2017, Ella released four EP’s, Troubled, Time, Change, and Ready. The three latest EP’s were released through Mustard’s record label, 10 Summers Records.

In 2018, Ella Mai released her self titled debut studio album, Ella Mai which debuted at #1 on the US R&B charts. The album included features from R&B artists such as Chris Brown, John Legend, and H.E.R.

Almost four years later, in May 2022, Ella released her sophomore studio album, Heart On My Sleeve which featured hit singles such as “Not Another Love Song,” and “DFMU.”

songs.title: Trip

description.plain:
After charting a top-five hit with “Boo’d Up” on the Hot 100, Ella Mai attempts to strike gold again with her new record “Trip.”
The piano-laden song finds Mai deeply entranced by the love she’s receiving in her relationship.

songs.title: Boo’d Up

description.plain:
In this song, Ella Mai is talking or referring to a specific “somebody” that has her feeling on top of the world. She likes being “Boo’d Up” with this person and she elaborates on that in the song.

“Boo’d Up” peaked at #5 on Billboard Hot 100 becoming Ella Mai’s first Top 10 on the chart. The song is nominated at the 61st Grammy Awards in the ‘Song of the Year’ and won “Best R&B Song' category.

This song is basically about how her ex met a girl in the club and it basically doesn’t bother her and she can never be compared to her in anyway,shape or form.
But in Ty Dolla $ign’s part he’s begging her not to leave and to change her mind on giving him another chance.
